body:
For the following Verilog code:
```verilog
module circuit(input clk, output reg [3:0] count);
  initial count = 4'h0; 
  always @(posedge clk)                                                                 
    count <= count + 1'b1;
endmodule
```
I get the following JSON description of the register:
```json
        "$procdff$4": {
          "hide_name": 1,
          "type": "$dff",
          "parameters": {
            "CLK_POLARITY": 1,
            "WIDTH": 4
          },
          "attributes": {
            "src": "/home/tilk/test/test.sv:3"
          },
          "port_directions": {
            "CLK": "input",
            "D": "input",
            "Q": "output"
          },
          "connections": {
            "CLK": [
              2
            ],
            "D": [
              7,
              8,
              9,
              10
            ],
            "Q": [
              3,
              4,
              5,
              6
            ]
          }
        }
      },
```
It does not include the initial value.
As I'm using the JSON output in [my simulator project](https://github.com/tilk/digitaljs), having the initial value in JSON output would allow me to simulate it.

